Japan Urged to Gain International Trust before Making Bid to Sit on UNSC 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- The Japanese ambassador to the UN, addressing the UN General Assembly recently, urged the reform of the UN Security Council and reiterated Japan's sustained efforts for it. This was nothing but an open revelation of Japan's sinister purpose to win a permanent seat on the Security Council through its expansion during the on-going UN session, observes Minju Joson Tuesday in a signed commentary.
 From a moral point of view it would be quite reasonable for Japan to seek permanent membership of the UN Security Council only after redressing all its unprecedented past crimes among other things to be trusted by other Asian countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan, however, leaves no means untried to sit on the UN Security Council and repeat its crime-woven history of aggression.
 The issue of Japan's bid for permanent membership of the UN Security Council can be discussed only after it has restored the trust of the Asian countries by sincerely repenting of its past wrongs. Japan can never calm down the deeply rooted bitterness and vigilance against it among the international community including the Asian countries nor can it gain the international community's trust in it unless it sincerely repents of its crime-woven past and fully apologizes and compensates for it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is by no means fortuitous that many countries in Asia and other parts of the world, to say nothing of Japan's allies are turning cold shoulders to Japan's bid for a permanent seat on the UNSC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan would be well advised to come to its senses, stop the foolish act that would invite denunciation and scorn and sincerely opt for settling its crime-woven past though belatedly.

"NA"'s Passage of Proposal on Rice Negotiations under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- The Federation of south Korean Trade Unions and the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification reportedly issued statements on Nov. 24 separately denouncing the south Korean "government" and ruling and opposition parties for railroading a proposal on rice negotiations through the "National Assembly".
 Noting that the opening of the rice market is a flunkeyist and treacherous act of meeting the interests of the U.S. only, the statement deplored the ceaseless death of farmers that resulted from the railroading of the "government"- introduced proposal through the "NA." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement urged the government to accept at once a 10-point demand for the defence of the rice sovereignty and the fundamental recovery of agriculture raised by farmers' organizations, declaring that the federation would firmly solidarize with the farmers' just struggle. 
 The south headquarters of the above-said alliance in the statement questioned the "Grand National Party" and the "Uri Party" what do they mean by "national interests". It went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "government", the GNP and the "Uri Party" should pay heed to the angry shouts of the south Koreans. You should bear in mind that the south Koreans' lives are dearer than the U.S. economy and the people's indignation is more fearful than its pressure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no room for you to remain in this land if you are not in a position to protect the people's lives.

Palestinians' Just Cause Supported 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- The Palestinian people's struggle to retake the territory usurped by the outsiders and build an independent and sovereign state is a just cause, says Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed article dedicated to the "day of world solidarity with the Palestinian people".
 On this day the Korean people extend firm solidarity and militant salute to the Palestinian people in their struggle to retake the territory usurped by the Israeli aggressors, build an independent state and achieve Mideast peace, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Palestinians formed several resistance organizations including the Palestinian National Liberation Movement and have waged struggles of various forms against the Israeli aggressors, registering many successes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Israel remains unchanged in its wild ambition to keep the Palestinian territory under its permanent occupation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international support and solidarity with the Palestinian people in their just cause have grown stronger as the days go by and this greatly encourages the Palestinians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people sincerely hope the Palestinian people will emerge victorious in their struggle to retake their legitimate national rights including the right to self-determination. The Korean people will as ever stand by the Palestinians and fully support and encourage them in their cause to build an independent state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world progressive people's support and solidarity with the Palestinians in their just cause will grow stronger.

Move to Extend Term of Presence of S. Korean Troops in Iraq Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification reportedly issued a statement on Nov. 24 denouncing the south Korean authorities for scheming to extend again the term of the presence of the south Korean troops in Iraq. 
 Recalling the fact that the "motion calling for extending again the term of the presence of the 'Jaitun' unit in Iraq" was placed on the agenda of the "National Assembly" on Nov. 21, the statement termed the "government's" persistant move to extend the term of their presence a product of their flunkeyist and treacherous behavior. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said move is little short of quelling the wishes of the people and their desire for independence for the purpose of meeting the requirements of the south Korea-U.S. "alliance", it noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement declared that the "NA" should never pass the "government"-introduced motion intended to force the south Koreans to fall victim to the alliance, not content with trampling down upon the workers and farmers' right to existence.

Rodong Sinmun on Servicepersons and People's Patriotic Devotion 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- Signal achievements made in building a rich and powerful country are the shining fruition of the ideological might of the servicepersons and people and their patriotic devotion, says Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed article.
 The Korean people were neither discouraged nor worried but built a powerful socialist country, independent in politics, self-sustaining in economy and self-reliant in national defence through their devoted creative labor under the leadership of the great party and the leader not with the help of others, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people's traditional and noble patriotic devotion has been fully displayed in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean People's Army has created assets of eternal value for the happiness of the people in the heroic self-sacrificing spirit, regarding it as their sacred duty to achieve the prosperity of the country, to say nothing of defending the country. Its total patriotic dedication is greatly encouraging all the people in their gigantic patriotic struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All of them have turned out as one in the general march for Songun revolution in the revolutionary soldier spirit and are devoting themselves to the patriotic labor for implementing the party's line and policy and building monumental edifices to be handed down to posterity.
 The construction drive waged by the servicepersons and people of the DPRK to attain the high goal of building a great prosperous powerful nation in the new century despite the worst adversity has been a bold offensive based on the do-or-die patriotic spirit and a heroic struggle for creation.
 The patriotic devotion displayed by the servicepersons and people in building a great prosperous powerful nation is an expression of their high pride and self-respect for the greatness of their socialist homeland. 
 The DPRK is the only country where the prosperity of the country and hope and happiness and beautiful future of individuals are interlinked. 
 Unshakable are the faith and will of the army and people of the DPRK to build a great prosperous powerful socialist country on this land at any cost with their wisdom, enthusiasm and by the sweat of their brow, a country to be envied by the world people

DPRK to Fulfill Its Commitment to Maritime Security and Protection of Sea Environment 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- The DPRK will as ever fulfill its noble duty in the work for the maritime security and the protection of sea environment as a member state of the International Maritime Organization. The head of the DPRK delegation to the 24th general assembly of the organization said this in his speech made on Nov. 22
 One of the important issues pending solution in the maritime field is to ensure coordination and impartiality in the way of implementing the standard of the organization, he noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  If the regulations of the maritime law to be newly adopted and effectuated are to be effectively implemented it is necessary to steadily narrow down the disparity among its member countries in the level of their development and capacity to implement them and to this end it is necessary to rejuvenate the organization's aid projects for creating the technological capability of the developing countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Last year the organization's technological aid surpassed the $ 14 million mark. This can be viewed as a very positive development but it is necessary to steadily increase the technological aid in the next fiscal year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The organization should not allow all forms of illegal acts of infringing upon the free navigation of sovereign states' ships and crews' personal safety under the pretext of combating "maritime terrorism" and unfair treatment toward ships and crew of other member states in a bid to achieve an unreasonable political aims. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The DPRK government has exerted great efforts to increase the capability of its maritime institution and taken necessary measures for it.
